Package com.barryholroyd.evermore.mapitems.mi_subclass Description

MiSubclass' store groups of related MapItems.

MiSubclass is the root of the class hierarchy. It is an abstract class extended by a number of subclasses.

Unlike the Evermore Mi* hierarchy, which consists of a tree of single class instances created during app initialization, MapItems are created dynamically during the life time of the app and are stored in collections associated with MiSubclasses (e.g., there is a collection of MapItem instances associated with MiSubclassContacts, a different collection of MapItem instances associated with MiSubclassSearch1, etc.).

Because MapItems are processed collectively, sometimes within a particular "collection" and sometimes across collections, they are not stored directly in the MiSunclass* instances. Instead, they are stored in the MapItemRegistry, along with their somewhat complex three-part ids.

In addition to indirectly owning a collection of MapItems via the MapItemRegistry, each MiSubclass* instance stores and icon and color used to represent its MapItems on the map. Where relevant, it may store other information (e.g., the text for the Search Buttons).

Since:
1.0
